          "prompt_html": "<h1>NOTE COMPLETION 33</h1><p><strong>Questions 24 - 30</strong></p><p>Complete the notes.</p><p>Use <strong>NO MORE THAN TWO WORDS</strong> for each answer.</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>UNIVERSITY OF BLEMFORD</strong><br><strong>COGNITIVE PSYCHOLOGY - RESEARCH PROJECT PLAN</strong><br><strong>COURSE CODE PS1820</strong></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>RESEARCH AREA</strong><br>Effects of olfactory stimuli on human behaviour (example - impact of coffee aroma on homebuyers).<br><strong>PURPOSE OF STUDY</strong><br>Determine whether <blank data-qid=\"q24\"/><br>is affected by the introduction of fragrances to a setting.<br><strong>PROPOSED METHOD</strong><br>Key <blank data-qid=\"q25\"/><br>= participant decision + fragrance used<br>- One fragrance considered to be pleasant<br>- Decision of participant - either quantitative ‘yes/no’ or <blank data-qid=\"q26\"/> scale<br>Location - two rooms - control must have neutral odour.<br><em><strong>Important - must ensure consistent fragrance_ <blank data-qid=\"q27\"/> _ _ <blank/><br>_</strong></em><br>| <strong>Participant Group A</strong> | <strong>Participant Group B</strong> |<br>| --- | --- |<br>| 1, Fragrance added to room | 1. No fragrance added to room |<br>| 2. Product <blank data-qid=\"q28\"/><br>3. Participant completes form - questions determine opinion of product |  |<br><strong>PARTICIPANTS</strong><br><blank data-qid=\"q29\"/> needs to be sufficient to establish significance - 24 participants in two groups.<br>Promoted through notice on portal and community website - include warning in case of <blank data-qid=\"q30\"/>.<br><strong>NOTES</strong><br>Remember to ask Professor Ingram about available rooms.</td></tr></tbody></table>",
